.TH GFT 1 "2026" "gft" "GitHub Fetch Tool"
.SH NAME
gft \- GitHub Fetch Tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gft
.I user/repo
.RI [ tag ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gft
is a lightweight command-line tool to fetch release information, list binary
assets, and download from any GitHub project \[em] without authentication.
.PP
It scrapes GitHub release pages directly, requiring no token setup and avoiding
API rate limit issues. When the
.B gh
CLI is installed and authenticated, gft uses it transparently as a fallback
for private repositories and richer JSON output.
.SH USAGE
.TP
.BI "gft " user/repo
Show latest release info
.TP
.BI "gft " "user/repo tag"
Show info for a specific release tag
.TP
.BI "gft " "user/repo v1.0..v2.0"
Compare two releases
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show gft version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-check\-update
Check if a newer version of gft is available.
.TP
.B \-\-upgrade
Upgrade gft to the latest version in-place.
.TP
.B \-\-assets
List binary release assets for the given tag.
.TP
.B \-\-detect
Auto-detect the best binary asset for your OS and architecture,
highlighting the recommended download in the asset list.
.TP
.BI \-\-get " pattern"
Download the asset whose name matches
.IR pattern .
If multiple assets match, an interactive selection prompt is shown.
.TP
.B \-\-install
Download, extract, and install the binary to your PATH automatically.
Uses
.B \-\-detect
to find the right asset when no
.B \-\-get
pattern is given.
.TP
.BR \-\-releases ", " \-\-list
List all available releases for the repository.
.TP
.B \-\-source " zip|tar"
Download the source archive non-interactively.
Accepts
.B zip
or
.B tar
(tar.gz) as argument. Suitable for use in scripts.
.TP
.BR \-\-checksum ", " \-\-verify
Verify the SHA-256 checksum of the downloaded file after
.B \-\-get
or
.BR \-\-install .
Looks for a companion checksum file among the release assets.
.TP
.B \-\-notes
Show the release notes for the resolved tag.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output release information as JSON. Uses the GitHub API via
.B gh
if available, otherwise builds JSON from scraped data.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Output the version tag only. Useful for scripting:
.B VERSION=$(gft nodejs/node -q)
.TP
.B \-\-pre
.PD 0
.TP
.B \-\-prerelease
.PD
Include pre-releases when resolving the latest tag.
By default, gft resolves to the latest stable release.
.TP
.B \-\-open
Open the release page in the default browser.
Combinable with other options (does not exit early).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output. Also honoured via the
.B NO_COLOR
environment variable.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Bypass the local response cache for this invocation.
.TP
.B \-\-clear\-cache
Clear all cached responses and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
When set to any value, disables colored output.
.TP
.B GITHUB_TOKEN
Optional GitHub personal access token. When set, gft uses it for API
requests, increasing the rate limit from 60 to 5000 requests per hour.
.TP
.B GFT_CACHE_TTL
Cache time-to-live in seconds (default: 300). Responses are cached in
.I ~/.config/gft/cache/
to avoid redundant network requests.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/gft/
Configuration and data directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/gft/VERSION
Installed version of gft.
.TP
.I ~/.config/gft/cache/
Cached HTTP responses (cleared by
.BR \-\-clear\-cache ).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Get latest release info:
.B gft cli/cli
.TP
Get a specific version:
.B gft nodejs/node v22.0.0
.TP
List all binary assets:
.B gft cli/cli --assets
.TP
Auto-detect the right binary:
.B gft cli/cli --detect
.TP
Download a specific asset:
.B gft cli/cli --get linux-amd64.deb
.TP
Download and install automatically:
.B gft cli/cli --install
.TP
Get version string for scripting:
.B VERSION=$(gft nodejs/node -q)
.TP
List all releases:
.B gft cli/cli --releases
.TP
List releases including pre-releases:
.B gft cli/cli --pre --releases
.TP
Show release notes:
.B gft cli/cli --notes
.TP
JSON output:
.B gft cli/cli --json
.TP
Download source as tar.gz (non-interactive):
.B gft cli/cli --source tar
.TP
Download and verify checksum:
.B gft cli/cli --get linux-amd64.tar.gz --checksum
.TP
Compare two releases:
.B gft cli/cli v2.40.0..v2.50.0
.TP
Open release page in browser:
.B gft cli/cli --open
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR curl (1),
.BR gh (1)
